another language.

"To modify" a work means to copy from or adapt all or part of the work in a
fashion requiring copyright permission, other than the making of an exact
copy. The resulting work is called a "modified version" of the earlier work or
a work "based on" the earlier work.

"You" means an individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

"Source code" for a work means the preferred form of the work for making
modifications to it.

"Object code" means any non-source form of a work.

"Standard Header" means a specific notice usually placed at the beginning of
each source file. It states that the file is released under the GNU GPL and
identifies the copyright holder.

